</section>
<section>
<header>
<p class="scripture-title" data-aid="154069264" id="scripture_title2"><a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/9?lang=eng&amp;id=p14-p23#p14">Alma 9:14&#x2013;23</a></p>
<h3 data-aid="154069270" id="title4">God&#x2019;s blessings come with great responsibility.</h3>
</header>
<p data-aid="154069276" id="p6">When reading about the way the Nephites in Ammonihah treated the Lord&#x2019;s servants, it is easy to forget that they once lived the gospel and were a &#x201C;highly favored people of the Lord&#x201D; (<a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/9?lang=eng&amp;id=p20#p20">Alma 9:20</a>). As you read about the great blessings God gave the people of Nephi (see especially <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/9?lang=eng&amp;id=p14-p23#p14">Alma 9:14&#x2013;23</a>), ponder the great blessings He has given you. What responsibilities come with these blessings? What are you doing to stay true to these responsibilities?</p>
<p data-aid="154069282" id="p7">See also <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/50?lang=eng&amp;id=p24#p24">Doctrine and Covenants 50:24</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/82?lang=eng&amp;id=p3#p3">82:3</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93?lang=eng&amp;id=p39#p39">93:39</a>.</p>
<div class="sc-bvqtyr-0 duiKkI video-vMiKm video"><div class="sc-bvqtyr-1 inwLwu"><div class="sc-bvqtyr-2 hQntbb"><img alt="" class="posterFallback-wNf54" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 320px, 640px" srcset="
            https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/imgs/https%3A%2F%2Fassets.churchofjesuschrist.org%2F8c%2F84%2F8c84222ffbcd600f7e1a3fe1a128828bdad5906a%2F8c84222ffbcd600f7e1a3fe1a128828bdad5906a.jpeg/full/!320,/0/default 320w,
